Suppose you have a **User** model and a corresponding repository name **UserRepository**:

    public interface UserRepository extends CrudRepository&lt;User, Long&gt; {}
     
Now create an instance of this UserRepository like:

    @Autowired
    private UserRepository userRepo;

Then update your User data:

    var user = userRepo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    user.setName(name); // password or email
    userRepo.save(user);

**Note**: CrudRepository interface has  **Optional&lt;T&gt; findById(ID id)** method definition.
Since Optional reference, If no user found it throws an exception, use orElseThrow().
